node.text:
Here’s how we use our Letter templates to add monograms to our charcuterie boards.
-
We attach our Letter Template to the board using @akfixna 705 and painters tape. Then we use a router with a @toolstoday 47222-S bit to pocket out the letter. 
Then we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast with @beaverdustpigments to fill the void. After it cures, a quick sand using @sia_abrasives_jjscanada sanding starting at 80 grit and finishing at 220 grit.
Last, we use some @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil to finish the board.
These acrylic templates are a great way to customize charcuterie boards for beginners and pros.
-
Shop wood, epoxy, templates, pigments and more at www.JeffMackSupply.com
-
#Acrylic #Epoxy #Template #Resin #WoodWorking #Custom #Charcuterie

node.text:
Looking for an easy DIY Project!?
-
We now have these letter templates available so you can create your own custom monogram boards!
-
This video shows the steps we take to create a piece like this.
-
Here’s what we used:
Here's What We Used:
WOOD: Roasted Maple (from our 4"-8" wide listing)
EPOXY: @squidpoxy Clear Fast (perfect for small pours like this)
PIGMENT: @blackdiamondpigments_com "White Diamond Effect"
TEMPLATES: 1/4" Large Round and the Letter "S" (we have the whole alphabet available now)

node.text:
Here’s how we use our Letter templates to add monograms to our charcuterie boards.
-
We attach our Letter Template to the board using @akfixna 705 and painters tape. Then we use a router with a @toolstoday 47222-S bit to pocket out the letter. 
Then we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast with @beaverdustpigments to fill the void. After it cures, a quick sand using @sia_abrasives_jjscanada sanding starting at 80 grit and finishing at 220 grit.
Last, we use some @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil to finish the board.
These acrylic templates are a great way to customize charcuterie boards for beginners and pros.
-

TEMPLATE FAQ’s!!
You’re going to want to save this one!
-
Q: What router bit do you use?
A: We use a @toolstoday 47222-s flush trim bit. It has a 3/16” bearing so you can route all the details in our templates.
-
Q: What epoxy do you use:
A: we use @squidpoxy Clear Fast. Cures in 24 hours so you can finish your piece the next day.
-
Q: What pigment do you use?
A: We have been using @beaverdustpigments metallic pigments lately and love them. Full collection available VERY SOON!
-
Q: What sandpaper do you use?
A: We use @sia_abrasives_jjscanada 6” sand paper. We sand from 80 grit up to 220 or 320 before oiling.
-
Q: What finish do you use?
A: We use @walrusoil Cutting Board Oil.
-
